msContents.summary: Lacunose copy of a commentary on al-Subkī's work on Islamic law; irregular foliation with frequent, large gaps that indicate missing text; some leaves may also be out of order.

title: Badr al-ṭāliʻ fī ḥall Jamʻ al-jawāmiʻ

persName.#text: Maḥallī, Jalāl al-Dīn Muḥammad ibn Aḥmad, 1389-1459
محلي، جلال الدين محمد بن احمد،
Subkī, Tāj al-Dīn ʻAbd al-Wahhāb ibn ʻAlī, approximately 1327-1370
سبكي، تاج الدين عبد الوهاب بن علي،

layoutDesc.layout: 17 lines per page; catchwords on versos, lower left.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in naskh in black ink; pointed.

origin.p: Item is undated, perhaps copied in the 14th or 15th century.

term: Islamic law--Interpretation and construction--Early works to 1800
